// Modules
mffs.guide.modules=Projector Modules

// Advanced Cube
mffs.guide.modules.advCube=Advanced Cube
mffs.guide.modules.advCube.1=This Projector module allows you to project a custom sized cube shaped module around the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.advCube.2=The projector will always be one block inside the center of one of face of the cube, depending on the orientation of the projector. When using the advanced cube, strength upgrades and focus matrix upgrades are used to determine the dimensions of the cube.
mffs.guide.modules.advCube.3=The strength upgrade determines how far from the projector the opposite face will be. The Focus Matrix within the four slots around the projector will determine how far from the projector each of the four side faces will be.
// Containment

mffs.guide.modules.containment=Containment
mffs.guide.modules.containment.1=This Projector module allows you to project a custom sized cube shaped module in front of the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.containment.2=The projector will always be one block in front, depending on the orientation of the projector. When using the containment, strength upgrades and focus matrix upgrades are used to determine the dimensions of the cube.
mffs.guide.modules.containment.3=The strength upgrade determines how far from the projector the opposite face will be. The Focus Matrix within the four slots around the projector will determine how far from the projector each of the four side faces will be.
mffs.guide.modules.containment.4=The distance upgrade determines how far from the projector the centre of the field will be.

mffs.guide.modules.cube=Cube
mffs.guide.modules.cube.1=This Projector module allows you to project a  cube shaped module around the projector. The distance upgrade determines how big the cube would be.

mffs.guide.modules.deflector=Deflector
mffs.guide.modules.deflector.1=This Projector module allows you to project a flat plane in front of the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.deflector.2=The Focus matrix within the four slots around the projector will determine how far from the projector each side of the field will be.
mffs.guide.modules.deflector.3=The Distrance upgrade determines how far from the projector the centre of the field will be.

mffs.guide.modules.wall=Wall
mffs.guide.modules.wall.1=This Projector module allows you to project 4 walls in front of the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.wall.2=The focus matrix within the four slots around the projector will determine how far from the projector each axis of the walls will be.
mffs.guide.modules.wall.3=The Distance upgrade determines how far from the projector the centre of the field will be. The strength upgrade determines how far from the start point the field will extend.

mffs.guide.modules.diagWall=Diagonal Wall
mffs.guide.modules.diagWall.1=This Projector module allows you to project 4 walls in front of the projector like the wall module,but diagonal instead of vertical.
mffs.guide.modules.diagWall.2=The focus matrix within the four slots around the projector will determine how far from the projector each axis of the walls will be.
mffs.guide.modules.diagWall.3=The Distance upgrade determines how far from the projector the centre of the field will be. The strength upgrade determines how far from the start point the field will extend.

mffs.guide.modules.sphere=Sphere
mffs.guide.modules.sphere.1=This projector module allows you to project a sphere around the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.sphere.2=The Distance upgrade determines the diameter of the sphere, while the strength upgrade determnes how thick the field will be.

mffs.guide.modules.tube=Tube
mffs.guide.modules.tube.1=This projector module allows you to project a tube around the projector.
mffs.guide.modules.tube.2=The Distance upgrade alters the length of the tube, while the Strength upgrade altars the size of the tube

